VERY SAVVY tracked the frontrunner just outside in the two path, two furlongs to go was asked for run but could not accelerate with the top two leaders and faded for a minor share in the final sixteenth. LOIS co-trailed on the inside in the beginning, was checked mildly losing momentum on the rail at the three eighths pole, hugged the rail to be in range at the top of the stretch but could not find another gear to be involved running to the wire inside. CLIFF'S HEAD settled in the middle of the pack outside three deep down the backside, was roused for more three furlongs from the finish making little headway and tired between rivals turning for home.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROOKIE RADAR broke awkwardly tossing the head a bit, moved forward stalking between runners in the second flight into the turn, exchanged repeated bumps with inside and outside foes at the three-eighths, moved out coming into upper stretch, struck the lead by the furlong marker and edged clear. BET N WIN settled off the pace, was asked to pick it up racing four wide at the five-sixteenths, shifted in a bit at the top of the stretch, rallied between rivals past the eighth pole and got up for second. BENLION hit the gate, was forwardly-positioned stalking the leading pair from outside three to four wide on the turn, loomed a threat in upper stretch but could not sustain the effort. COLLABORATIVE was bumped into the outside rival at the start, steadied and altered outside a rival in front who had checked at the three-eighths, subsequently went four wide on the turn, kept on to get up for the super. TRIGGER'S BAY broke outwardly bumping a rival and bothering others at the start, was coaxed forward and switched out stalking the leader into the turn, pressed from outside on that bend, took a brief and narrow lead past the quarter pole but faltered in the stretch. IGNITE THE STORM hit the gate, moved to the lead soon after the start and angled in clearing the gap, set the pace inside, weakened. DAWSON SILVER was bumped and steadied at the start, settled at the back outside, went four then five wide on the turn, failed to menace. DEFOGGER moved forward inside tracking from the second flight into the turn, exchanged several bumps at the three-eighths then checked sharply to drop back to last, was not a threat thereafter. WILD CONVERSATION was bumped into a rival at the start, stalked from outside the second flight into the turn, exchanged some bumps at the three-eighths, faded. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO BOTH THE START AND THE INCIDENT NEAR THE THREE-EIGHTHS POLE, AS WELL AS AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF DEFOGGER AGAINST WILD CONVERSATION ALLEGING INTERFERENCE AT THAT POINT, THE OBJECTION WAS NOT ALLOWED BUT TRIGGER'S BAY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIFTH AND PLACED LAST BEHIND WILD CONVERSATION FOR BOTHERING THAT ONE AND OTHERS AT THE START.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SACRED DANCER was smartly reined back off the speed duel up front down the backstretch, had a clear run on the fence gaining quickly on foes throughout the turn, bid for the lead inside at the eighth pole and drifted out under the drive to win in a photo at the finish. HARD EDGE was part of the four pronged fight for the lead outside, fought stubbornly through the turn four wide setting the fractions, poked her head in front in the five path at the furlong marker and lost the nod to the fast closing winner at the wire. BREATHING FIRE was bounced around between foes at the start trailing down the backside, began to pick up runners three wide outside with five sixteenths left to run, shifted out in upper stretch to the six path under left handed urging, was full of run late and closed to be a solid third after the compromised beginning. ZANA travelled in midfield four deep at the half, waited behind the wall of engaging frontrunners with three eighths to go, roused at the quarter pole keeping pace and finished up willingly down the lane to settle for a small share crossing the line. OL' BLONDIE stalked near the rear outside down the backstretch, put in a good move around horses four wide with three furlongs to go, was in the hunt widest in the six path for the drive but levelled off with a sixteenth to run. CANADIANSWEETHEART had a slim advantage on the rail hounded outside by three other rivals in the early going, continued to press on up front throughout the turn inside, had a narrow lead at the top of the lane, could not hold off the closers in mid-stretch and yielded in the final furlong. CURLIN CANDY was part of the early pace in the two path fighting with three others for the front down the backside, gave way with runners on either side midway on the turn and could not find more straightening out for the drive to be involved at the wire. INDIAN MUSIC eased off the contesting front four with seven sixteenths from home, was shuffled back losing position tracking through the turn and could not become a factor in the stretch drive. SOUPER SUNDAY was part of the four horses vying for the lead in the early going three wide between foes, steadied sharply in tight quarters dueling for the lead with rivals on either side midway on the turn and could not recover to be involved down the lane. STEWARDS INQUIRY REGARDING #8 SOUPER SUNDAY AROUND THE THREE FURLONG MARKER RESULTED IN NO CHANGE

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 94. Claiming Purse 54500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIGHT THE LAMP tracked the early speed in the beginning, took up the running to press outside up front at the half, contested two wide throughout the turn fighting for the lead, began to edge away from early rival while lugging in under left hand urging at the furlong pole and held safe by a diminishing margin at the wire. SOUPER CLASSY settled near the rear in the three path at the half mile pole, waited while in tight briefly with three eighths remaining, rallied up the fence with a quarter left to the finish, shifted out for the stretch run in the four path and closed late but could not get there in time. EMICRACK (CHI) travelled three deep tracking down the backside, was in a good spot keeping eyes on the engaging front two three furlongs from the wire, was hard ridden between quickening rivals two furlongs from the prize and finished up late to close in for third catching the early speed horse nearing the wire. LUV TO WIN was away alertly to take command angling in to the rail by the half mile marker, was headed outside by the winner with three furlongs from home, battled stubbornly inside until the furlong marker and gave way in deep stretch. COMMANDER JOE broke in, stumbling mildly at the start, offered an early move four deep outside down the backside, rallied into the turn going four wide around foes at the three furlong marker, could not sustain the run straightening out for the stretch drive and levelled off in midstretch. HAPPYMAC tracked on the rail early on, clipped heels stumbling on the rail at the half, regrouped on the fence entering the turn, was shuffled inside not keeping up with others three furlongs to go and could not be a presence in the stretch. KING ALFREDO was bumped outside at the break, co-trailed on the rail in the beginning, shifted outside three deep between foes at the half, could not maintain position with rallying rival outside into turn, made little headway on horses with a quarter to run and showed little driving to the wire. STEWARDS INQUIRY AND RIDERS CLAIM OF FOUL #3 HAPPYMAC AGAINST #7 LUV TO WIN DOWN THE BACKSTRETCH WAS DISALLOWED RESULTING IN NO CHANGE

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 12 1M Turf CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 111000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $9,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR RESTRICTED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $32,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000, if for $30,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Any Maiden Races, And Only Claiming Races And Only Starter Races For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPSASIONAL got away alertly, settled in to stalk the pacesetter two to three wide on the turn, bid at the quarter pole, edged away, held. WHAT SAY THEE settled at the rear early, advanced between runners two to three wide into and on the turn, shifted five wide into upper stretch, gained steadily while drifting in just a bit, was second best. TIDAL FORCES stalked from between runners three wide early, moved out four wide coming to the top of the stretch with aim, kicked on mildly. A THREAD OF BLUE dropped back racing off the inside, was last into the turn going three wide, came out a bit at the three-sixteenths, continued to gain late. DOWNY BOY tracked in behind racing in the two path on the turn, ran on evenly. PERFECT CRIME chased from outside four wide, encouraged along midway on the turn, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, made no late bid and ran on evenly. KING ELVIS sped clear, set the pace inside, gave way. GRAND JOURNEY bumped a rival at the start, chased from outside mid-pack, went four then five wide on the turn, fanned eight wide into upper stretch, failed to rally. IT'S A FLUKE broke a step slowly and was bumped at the start, thereupon angled in, saved ground toward the back and was never near enough to threaten.
